      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sound 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the legendary 13B-REW rotary powerplant. This example retains its complex sequential twin-turbocharger setup, delivering a smooth torque curve and high-RPM urgency. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a five-speed manual transmission and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by the original double-wishbone suspension architecture, providing precise turn-in and tactile feedback. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system refresh with an upgraded aluminum radiator to optimize thermal management. Compression results are consistent across all rotor faces, indicating healthy apex seals and internal housing integrity. The exterior displays minor road wear consistent with enthusiast use, but the structural rigidity and drivetrain performance remain uncompromised.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    }
